    <body>
      <div xml:id="NA107-kiḷavi">
        <p type="edition">itu piriviṭai melinta talaivi tōḻikkuc colliyatu.</p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">This is what SHE who had weakened during the separation said to [her] confidante.</p>
      </div>
      <div xml:id="NA107">
        <lg type="edition">
<l>            uḷḷutoṟu nakuvēṉ tōḻi vaḷḷukirp</l>
<l>            piṭipiḷan tiṭṭa nāril veṇkōṭṭuk</l>
<l>            koṭiṟupōl kāya vāliṇarp pālaic</l>
<l>            celvaḷi tūkkali ṉilaitīr neṟṟaṅ</l>
<l>            kalliḻi yaruviyi ṉolleṉa volikkum </l>
<l>            pullilai yōmaiya pulivaḻaṅ kattañ</l>
<l>            ceṉṟa kātalar vaḻivaḻip paṭṭa</l>
<l>            neñcē nalviṉaip pāṟṟē yīṇṭoḻin</l>
<l>            tāṉāk kauvai malainta</l>
<l>            yāṉē tōḻi nōyppā lēṉē.</l>
    </lg>
       <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>Whenever I remember I smile, friend:<note place="foot">This formulaic start (cf. NA 100.1) does not seem to fit the context of this poem at all. Syntax too seems a little awkward. We would like a direct object for <term xml:lang="ta">uḷḷutoṟum</term>, and we would expect it at the end of the poem.</note></l>
<l rend="indent4">[My] heart,</l>
<l rend="indent2">that set out to the lover who had gone</l>
<l rend="indent2">on the road where tigers roam, with low-leaved Ōmai trees,</l>
<l rend="indent">where the leafless<note place="foot"><term xml:lang="ta">lai tīr</term> presumably has to be taken as an elliptical epithet: the branches on which the nuts are hanging have lost their leaves, not the nuts themselves.</note> nuts, when the moving wind lifts [them]</l>
<l rend="indent">on the Pālai trees with pure clusters [and] unripe fruits, like pincers,</l>
<l rend="indent3">[its] barkless white branches split [and] put aside</l>
<l rend="indent3">by the sharp-nailed she-elephant,</l>
<l rend="indent">sound 'ol' like the waterfall descending from the stones,</l>
<l>good work [was] its part.</l>
<l rend="indent4">As for me,</l>
<l rend="indent2">who was opposed by unending 
 <choice>   
    <seg>scandal</seg>
    <seg>affliction</seg>
</choice>
    , staying behind here,</l>
<l>my part, friend, [was] pain.</l>
        </lg>
